<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>WindowServer • Easy Guide</title>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&amp;family=Space+Grotesk:wght@500;600&amp;display=swap');
        
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', system_ui, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 820px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f8f9fc;
            color: #1f2937;
        }
        
        h1, h2, h3 {
            font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system_ui, sans-serif;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        
        .header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 32px;
        }
        
        .header h1 {
            font-size: 2.6rem;
            margin: 0;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #0066ff, #3388ff);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }
        
        .card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 26px;
            margin-bottom: 22px;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
        }
        
        .section-title {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            margin: 0 0 14px 0;
        }
        
        .hotkey {
            background: #111827;
            color: white;
            padding: 5px 12px;
            border-radius: 7px;
            font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }
        
        .illustration {
            background: #f8fafc;
            border: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 18px;
            margin: 14px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        
        .step {
            display: flex;
            gap: 14px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }
        
        .step-number {
            background: #0066ff;
            color: white;
            width: 26px;
            height: 26px;
            border-radius: 9999px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-weight: 700;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
        }
        
        .highlight {
            background: #f0f7ff;
            border-left: 4px solid #0066ff;
            padding: 14px 18px;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        
        .mouse-demo {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 32px;
            margin: 16px 0;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        
        .mouse-box {
            width: 130px;
            height: 82px;
            background: white;
            border: 2px solid #cbd5e1;
            border-radius: 10px;
            position: relative;
            box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
        }
        
        .mouse-cursor {
            position: absolute;
            width: 16px;
            height: 16px;
            background: #0066ff;
            border-radius: 50%;
            box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(0, 102, 255, 0.25);
            transition: all 1.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
        }
        
        .label {
            font-size: 0.82rem;
            color: #64748b;
            margin-top: 6px;
            font-weight: 500;
        }
        
        .stealth {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #dcfce7;
            color: #166534;
            padding: 3px 10px;
            border-radius: 9999px;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        
        .tip {
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #475569;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="header">
        <h1>WindowServer</h1>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #64748b; margin-top: 4px;">The most stealthy exam assistant for macOS</p>
    </div>

    <!-- What makes it special -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">Why This App is Extremely Stealthy</h2>
        <p>It uses private SkyLight APIs to capture exactly what you see on screen — bypassing most normal screenshot blocks used by exam software.</p>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 12px;">
            <span class="stealth">Uses SkyLight private API</span>
            <span class="stealth" style="margin-left: 8px;">Runs as "WindowServer"</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Get API Key -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">1. Get Your Free Gemini API Key</h2>
        
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Go to <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey" target="_blank" style="color:#0066ff; font-weight:600;">Google AI Studio</a></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Click <strong>Create API Key</strong> and copy it</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div>Paste it in Settings (<span class="hotkey">Ctrl + E</span>). It saves automatically.</div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Virtual Display -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">2. Create Virtual Display (Highly Recommended)</h2>
        
        <p>The virtual display pretends to be a real external monitor. This makes the app much harder to detect.</p>
        
        <div class="highlight">
            <strong>Best Stealth Practice:</strong><br>
            Open <strong>Bluebook</strong> or <strong>Lockdown Browser</strong> <strong>inside</strong> the virtual display. 
            The exam software will think it's running on a normal external monitor.
        </div>

        <div class="step" style="margin-top:16px;">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + E</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Enable Virtual Display and click <strong>Create Virtual Display</strong></div>
        </div>

        <div class="illustration">
            After creating it, go to <strong>System Settings → Displays</strong>.<br>
            You’ll see a new monitor called <strong>LG UltraFine 5K</strong>.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Hotkeys -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">3. Hotkeys</h2>
        
        <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:12px;">
            <div style="background:#f8fafc; padding:14px; border-radius:10px;">
                <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + A</span><br>
                <strong>Capture screen + send to Gemini</strong>
            </div>
            <div style="background:#f8fafc; padding:14px; border-radius:10px;">
                <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + V</span><br>
                <strong>Automatically type the answer</strong>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <p class="tip" style="margin-top:14px;">
            Just press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + A</span> while in your exam. The app captures stealthily and sends it to AI.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- How to Answer Questions -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">4. How to Answer Questions (Live Demo)</h2>
        
        <p>When Gemini detects a multiple choice question, your mouse automatically moves to the correct answer.</p>
        
        <div class="illustration">
            <strong>Live Mouse Teleport</strong>
            
            <div class="mouse-demo">
                <!-- A -->
                <div>
                    <div class="mouse-box">
                        <div class="mouse-cursor" style="left:22px; top:22px; animation: moveToA 2.8s infinite ease-in-out;"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="label"><strong>A</strong> — Top Left</div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- B -->
                <div>
                    <div class="mouse-box">
                        <div class="mouse-cursor" style="left:90px; top:22px; animation: moveToB 2.8s infinite ease-in-out;"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="label"><strong>B</strong> — Top Right</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <style>
            @keyframes moveToA {
                0%, 100% { left: 22px; top: 22px; }
                50% { left: 22px; top: 52px; }
            }
            @keyframes moveToB {
                0%, 100% { left: 90px; top: 22px; }
                50% { left: 90px; top: 52px; }
            }
        </style>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="background:#f0f7ff; border:1px solid #bfdbfe;">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0; color:#1e40af;">Quick Summary</h3>
        <ul style="margin:8px 0 0 18px; padding:0;">
            <li>Use Virtual Display + open Bluebook/Lockdown inside it for maximum stealth</li>
            <li>Press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + A</span> to capture and get AI help</li>
            <li>Press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + V</span> to type the answer</li>
            <li>Mouse auto-moves to the correct MCQ answer</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <p style="text-align:center; color:#94a3b8; font-size:0.85rem; margin-top:32px;">
        WindowServer.app • Extremely stealthy by design
    </p>

</body>
</html>
